( 8. Rationale and generalization) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The heuristic model is transparent and easy to convert into policy. Only exact time-to-) Tj
T*
(click reuse uses percentile calibration because it is a global duplicate-count signal) Tj
T*
(whose suspiciousness depends on the dataset's observed timer granularity and reuse) Tj
T*
(distribution; the absolute floor protects against weak duplicate counts in smaller or) Tj
T*
(smoother datasets. Other heuristic cutoffs remain fixed or total-rate based because they) Tj
T*
(represent separate behavioral concepts. The time-to-click timing bands are intentionally) Tj
T*
(tiered: clicks from 0 to 250 ms are treated as implausibly fast direct evidence, clicks) Tj
T*
(from 20 to 60 seconds add low-weight support for delayed or mechanical click patterns,) Tj
T*
(and clicks above 120 seconds remain a separate extreme timing signal. The regular inter-) Tj
T*
(arrival rule is intentionally narrow because the dataset has no explicit user or session) Tj
T*
(identifier: it only compares clicks with the same region, browser, OS, query, and) Tj
T*
(clicked domain, requires at least eight events, and adds low-weight supporting evidence) Tj
T*
(rather than a standalone bot decision. Structured rule contributions include) Tj
T*
(threshold_mode, with fixed rules reported as absolute and adaptive exact-ttc reuse) Tj
T*
(reported as adaptive_percentile when present. The Isolation Forest model catches) Tj
T*
(multivariate oddities that a small rule set may miss. Both should generalize when bot) Tj
T*
(traffic is repetitive or mechanically timed, but they may miss human-like bots and may) Tj
T*
(over-flag legitimate campaigns that naturally produce high repetition. The thresholds) Tj
T*
(should be recalibrated when traffic mix, geography, or ad inventory changes materially.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
( 9. Probability assessment) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(The estimated probability that a flagged event is fraudulent is 79%. This is not label-) Tj
T*
(calibrated precision; it is a reasoned estimate based on agreement between independent) Tj
T*
(signals. Events flagged by both the heuristic model and the upper tail of the ML anomaly) Tj
T*
(score are more likely to be fraudulent than events flagged by only one weak signal. The) Tj
T*
(report therefore treats probability as an operational confidence estimate, not a) Tj
T*
