T*
() Tj
T*
(- The dataset has no ground-truth bot labels, so Bot Hunter cannot report measured) Tj
T*
(precision, recall, or calibration.) Tj
T*
(- The rules intentionally favor interpretable repetition and timing signals. Human-like) Tj
T*
(automation, slow distributed bot traffic, or attacks spread across many query/domain) Tj
T*
(combinations may be under-detected.) Tj
T*
(- Legitimate campaigns can create high repetition, dense device clusters, or) Tj
T*
(synchronized bursts. The suppress tier should therefore be policy-approved and) Tj
T*
(periodically sampled.) Tj
T*
(- The regular inter-arrival rule uses narrow pseudo-session groups because there is no) Tj
T*
(user or session identifier. It is supporting evidence rather than proof of automation.) Tj
T*
(- The anomaly score is relative to the current traffic mix. Material changes in) Tj
T*
(geography, inventory, campaign volume, browser mix, or feature extraction should trigger) Tj
T*
(a fresh threshold and review calibration.) Tj
